The paper focuses on a new approach and design model for performance budgets for timing and energy consumption, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and embedded systems (cs.EM). The use of Petri Nets formalism suggests a systems and control theory perspective (cs.SY), while the focus on decreasing cognitive load suggests a programming languages (cs.PL) or logic in computer science (cs.LO) perspective.
